  "description": "Redevelopment of the site to provide an adult mental health\r\nunit comprising in-patient wards; support and therapy\r\ndepartments; a day hospital; education and treatment\r\nfacilities; and associated landscaping works and provision\r\nof parking areas.\r\nAs shown on drawing nos. 3204/D/01B, 010A, 011A, 012A,\r\n013A, 014A, 015A, 016, 102A, 110G, 100, 111I, 112E, 113E,\r\n114A, 115D, 116C, 117B, 119, 120A, 121A, 122A, 124A, 125,\r\n126A, 127A - revised by agent's letters dated 14.12.1999 and\r\n17.12.1999 - Planning Statement Ref 1467.1, Transportation\r\nStatement dated 17.12.1999, NHS Trust statement \"Providing\r\nand Effective and Safe Hospital Facility for Local People\r\nwith Mental Health Problems, Landscape Statement 626/D/1 Rev\r\nA, Tree Schedule Rev B dated 24.8.99",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "Condition : 1 - The details of the [layout, sections, elevations and facing materials] to be used on the building shall not be otherwise than as shall have been submitted to and approved by the Council before any work is commenced on the relevant part of the development. [Such details shall include proposed slab levels of the building in relation to the existing and proposed levels of the site and the surrounding land.] These parts of the development shall not be carried out otherwise than in accordance with the details thus approved.\r\n\r\nReason: To safeguard the appearance of the premises and the character of the immediate area in accordance with the requirements of policies EN1 and EN13 [and EN31 if in a CA] of the London Borough of Camden Unitary Development Plan 2000.\r\n",
    "Condition : 2 - The detailed design of the elevations shall not be otherwise than as shall have been submitted to and approved by the Council before the work is commenced.",
    "Condition : 3 - No development, including works of demolition of parts of\r\n    Blocks M and K, shall take place before a schedule of works\r\n    of restoration to the retained parts of Blocks M and K\r\n    together with appropriate drawings has been submitted to and\r\n    approved in writing by the Council.",
    "Condition : 4 - No development shall take place before a schedule of\r\n    materials to be salvaged, method statement for their storage\r\n    and proposals for their re-use have been  submitted to and\r\n    approved in writing by the Council.",
    "Condition : 5 - No development shall take place until full details of hard and soft landscaping and means of enclosure of all un-built, open areas have been submitted to and approved by the Council. [Such details shall include details of any proposed earthworks including grading, mounding and other changes in ground levels.] \r\n\r\nReason: To enable the Council to ensure a reasonable standard of visual amenity in the scheme in accordance with the requirements of policies [EN15 if landscape details], [EN61 if trees only] [and EN35 if in a CA] of the London Borough of Camden Unitary Development Plan 2000.\r\n",
    "Condition : 6 - All hard and soft landscaping works shall be carried out to a reasonable standard in accordance with the approved landscape details [by not later than the end of the planting season following completion of the development or any phase of the development] [, prior to the occupation for the permitted use of the development or any phase of the development], whichever is the sooner. Any trees or areas of planting which, within a period of 5 years from the completion of the development, die, are removed or become seriously damaged or diseased, shall be replaced as soon as is reasonably possible and, in any case, by not later than the end of the following planting season, with others of similar size and species, unless the Council gives written consent to any variation.\r\n\r\nReason: To ensure that the landscaping is carried out within a reasonable period and to maintain a satisfactory standard of visual amenity in the scheme in accordance with the requirements of policies EN15 [and EN35 if in a CA] of the London Borough of Camden Unitary Development Plan 2000.\r\n",
    "Condition : 7 - No development shall take place before a method statement\r\n    detailling the installation of the proposed oil storage\r\n    tank, and including details of the use of the oil to be\r\n    stored there, and proposed mitigating measures in the event\r\n    of any leakage has been submitted to and approved in writing\r\n    by the Council.",
    "Condition : 8 - No development shall take place before details of the\r\n    proposed elevations for Block K have been submitted to and\r\n    approved in writing by the Council.",
    "Condition : 9 - To ensure that the Council may be satisfied with the\r\n    external appearance of the building.",
    "Condition : 10 - To ensure that the Council may be satisfied with the\r\n    external appearance of the building.",
    "Condition : 11 - To ensure that the Council may be satisfied with the\r\n    external appearance of the building.",
    "Condition : 12 - To ensure that the Council may be satisfied with the methods\r\n    and proposals.",
    "Condition : 13 - In order that the Council may give consideration to the\r\n    details of the proposed development.",
    "Condition : 14 - To ensure that the landscaping is carried out within a\r\n    reasonable period and to maintain a satisfactory standard of\r\n    visual amenity in the scheme.",
    "Condition : 15 - To safeguard the amenities of the adjoining premises and the\r\n    area generally.",
    "Condition : 16 - To ensure that the Council may be satisfied with the\r\n    appearance of the proposal and its effect upon the\r\n    conservation area and adjoining listed cemetery.",
    "Condition : 17 - Please contact Robin Harper, the Council's Principal Design\r\n    and Conservation Officer, (Tel 020 7974 1944) in respect of\r\n    conditions 1,2,3,4 and 8 of PE9900500R1 and PE9900579R1 and\r\n    conditions 2 and 3 of CE9900501R1 and CE9900580R1.",
    "Condition : 18 - In good time, prior to the start of construction (or if\r\n    appropriate, demolition) on site, the contractor shall\r\n    discuss and agree with the Council's Streets Management\r\n    Traffic Management Section (tel:020-7974 5629) detailed\r\n    arrangements for the transportation of goods and materials\r\n    to and from the site. The Council will prosecute those\r\n    responsible for any breaches of the provisions of the\r\n    Highways and Litter Acts which occur as a result of\r\n    construction on the site.",
    "Condition : 19 - Works of construction and ancillary activity should not take\r\n    place other than between the hours of 08.00am to 18.00 pm on\r\n    Monday to Friday and 08.00am to 13.00pm on Saturday, with no\r\n    working on Sunday or Bank Holidays, in order to comply with\r\n    locally enforced standards.",
    "Condition : 20 - Noise from demolition and construction works is subject to\r\n    control under the Control of Pollution Act 1974. You are\r\n    advised to consult the Council's Environmen and Consumer\r\n    Service (Pollution Team), Camden Town Hall, Argyle Street,\r\n    WC1H 8EQ, (tel: 020 7278 4444), or to seek prior approval\r\n    under Section 61 if you anticipate any difficulty  in\r\n    carrying out construction other than within normal\r\n    working hours and by means that would minimise disturbance\r\n    to adjoining premises.",
    "Condition : 21 - Your attention is drawn to the fact that there is a separate\r\n    legal agreement with the Council which relates to the\r\n    development for which this permission is granted.",
    "Condition : 22 - The details required pursuant to Condition(s) 1, 2, 3, 4, 5,\r\n    7, 8 of the planning permission should be submitted with the\r\n    attached approval of details application form together with\r\n    5 sets of drawings and any other supporting information.",
    "Condition : 23 - The council is anxious to secure the long-term future of the\r\n    retained section ob Block K.  Therefore, the applicants are\r\n    requested to consider all possible options, including use\r\n    for nurses accommodation, and to inform the Council of their\r\n    intentions."
  ],
